<br>
If you only block ;lkasjdfou01@spam.mailer.com then they change it by one letter and it goes through, but if you block @spam.mailer.com then they have to change the domain name (which costs them money) to get through.<br>
<br>
1.        open outlook express<br>
2.        click tools, message rules, mail<br>
3.        click new, or edit an existing rule<br>
4.        make sure the first selection “Where the From line contains these people” is checked<br>
5.        in the second box, scroll to the end and check “delete it from the server”<br>
6.        in the third box, click on the blue underlined “contains people”<br>
7.        in the top box, type in or paste the @domain.com address of the spam mail you want blocked.<br>
8.        click add (repeat 7, 8 until you have all addresses, you can add more later of course)<br>
9.        click ok, ok, ok<br>
10.        To modify the list, or remove a name from the list, you can click on the rule, then modify and adjust/add names to it.<br>
<br>
Oh, I should mention where to get the email/domain name to block. Open the spam message, right click on the &quot;from&quot; address and copy it from there. The name you see in &quot;from&quot; is not always the actual domain name you need to block, so make sure you right click and copy from there.<br>
